NAME - ::<namespace>:: emulation_efm_config

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

Configures EFM emulation for a given port. Also has the ability to toggle certain EFM

SYNOPSIS - ::<namespace>::emulation_efm_config

List arguments in the alphabetical order or in the reverse alphabetical order.

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-port_handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork [M] , IxOS/IxNetwork-FT [M]

DESCRIPTION

Port to configure EFM emulation messages on.(DEFAULT = N/A)

DEFAULT

 None

-critical_event

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Send Critical Event message to EFM peer. Enables critical event flag on all OAMPDUs. When IxNetwork/IxProtocol Tcl Api is used, this parameter configures the OAMPDUs from the current EFM Link.With IxNetwork/IxProtocol TCL API this parameter will be updated even if the protocol is running.(DEFAULT = 0)

DEFAULT

 None

-dying_gasp

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Send Dying Gasp message to EFM peer. Enables dying gasp flag on all all OAMPDUs. When IxNetwork/IxProtocol Tcl Api is used, this parameter configures the OAMPDUs from the current EFM Link.With IxNetwork/IxProtocol TCL API this parameter will be updated even if the protocol is running.(DEFAULT = 0)

DEFAULT

 None

-error_frame_period_threshold

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Define the threshold for Errored Frame Period Events. Builds an OAMPDU code 'Event Notification' and adds an error_frame_period TLV to it, or appends an error_frame_period TLV to the existing OAMPDU.When IxNetwork/IxProtocol Tcl Api is used, one EFM Link can have only one 'Event Notification' OAMPDU. If none of the error_frame, error_frame_period, error_frame_summary, error_symbol_period TLV parameters are specified than the EFM Link will have no 'Event Notification' OAMPDU. This parameter enables the error_frame_period TLV on the 'Event Notification' OAMPDU and configures its threshold value. With IxNetwork/IxProtocol TCL API this parameter will be updated even if the protocol is running.(DEFAULT = 30)

DEFAULT

 None

-error_frame_period_window

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

If none of the error_frame, error_frame_period, error_frame_summary, error_symbol_period TLV parameters are specified than the EFM Link will have no 'Event Notification' OAMPDU. This parameter enables the error_frame_period TLV on the 'Event Notification' OAMPDU and configures its window value. With IxNetwork/IxProtocol TCL API this parameter will be updated even if the protocol is running. (DEFAULT = 300)

DEFAULT

-size

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

The size of the OAMPDU datagrams to send. When IxNetwork/IxProtocol Tcl Api is used, this parameter configures the maximum OAMPDU size for this EFM Link.(DEFAULT = 64)

DEFAULT

 None

-variable_retrieval

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Specify that TGEN EFM emulation should have variable retrieval enabled. Creates an OAMPDU with code "Information" having variable retrieval capability flag enabled. When IxNetwork/IxProtocol Tcl Api is used, the OAMPDUs with code "Information" are controlled by the Ixia port. They cannot be send on demand. When EFM emulation is started, the EFM Link will use send the Information OAMPDUs accordingly to establish discovery.With IxNetwork/IxProtocol TCL API this parameter will be updated even if the protocol is running.(DEFAULT = 0)

DEFAULT

 None

-vsi_value

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Allows configuration of the vendor specific information on the Ixia port. 8 HEX chars. When IxNetwork/IxProtocol Tcl API is used, this parameter configures the vendor specific information for this EFM Link.

DEFAULT

 None

-api_used

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

Not defined

Valid options are:

ixnetwork

Use IxNetwork implementation. Valid only if the HLTSET used loads IxNetwork TCL API.

x

Use IxNetwork implementation. Valid only if the HLTSET used loads IxNetwork TCL API.

ixprotocol

Use IxProtocol implementation. Valid only if the HLTSET used loads IxProtocol TCL API.

ixos

Use IxOS implementation. This is the default if the HLTSET does not load

DEFAULT

 None

0

DEFAULT

0

-enable_variable_response

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

-length_mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Not supported with IxTclNetwork.fixed - The OAMPDU size is fixed. Size of the OAMPDU is configured using the -size argument.random - The OAMPDU size is random. The minimum value will be the minimum needed to fit the OAMPDU. The maximum value will be specified using the -size argument. If the -size argument is smaller than the minimum size required to fit the OAMPDU, the value will be fixed and set to the value of the size argument.

DEFAULT

random

single

-oampdu_type

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Not supported with IxNetwork/IxProtocol Tcl API. Configures the OAMPDU types that will be configured. When IxNetwork/IxProtocol Tcl API is used, Information OAMPDUs are controlled by the Ixia port and send accordingly to accomplish discovery. Only one Event Notification OAMPDU is created per EFM Link.

Valid options are:

none

only configure OAM port properties. Does not create any OAMPDUs.

information

creates an Information OAMPDU

event_notification

creates an Event Notification OAMPDU

info_and_event

creates an Information OAMPDU and an Event Notification OAMPDU

DEFAULT

info_and_event

-os_event_tlv_oui

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Supported only with IxNetwork/IxProtocol Tcl Api. Three octets field in hex. Organizationally Unique Identifier for Organization Specific Event TLV.With IxNetwork/IxProtocol TCL API this parameter will be updated even if the protocol is running.

DEFAULT

0x000100

-os_event_tlv_value

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Supported only with IxNetwork/IxProtocol Tcl Api. This field indicates the value of the Organization Specific Event. This field's length is unspecified. Any hex value can be given (use 0x0011 format).With IxNetwork/IxProtocol TCL API this parameter will be updated even if the protocol is running.

DEFAULT

0x00

This parameter enables the error_symbol_period TLV on the 'Event Notification' OAMPDU and configures its count value.With IxNetwork/IxProtocol TCL API this parameter will be updated even if the protocol is running.(DEFAULT = 50)

DEFAULT
